Special Assistant to the President and Coordinator for the Southwest Border, Ambassador Roberta Jacobson, along with Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for the Western Hemisphere Juan Gonzalez, will travel to Mexico and Guatemala to address migration issues. In Mexico, they will work with government officials to develop a plan to manage migration effectively and humanely. In Guatemala, Senior Director Gonzalez will meet with government officials, civil society representatives, and non-government organizations to address the root causes of migration and build a better future in the region. They will be joined by Department of State Northern Triangle Special Envoy Ricardo Zuniga.